M||tx|---
M||titl|Lift State into pr cp
M||impa|hi
M||impa|enables state sharing outside cp boundaries
M||tags|composition, state, context, pr
M||tx|---
M|Lift|tx|Move state management into dedicated pr cp. This allows sibling
M|Lift|tx|cp outside the main UI to access and modify state w/o prop drilling
M|Lift|tx|or awkward refs.
M|Lift|**In|**
M|Lift|tx|```tsx
M|Lift|tx|fn ForwardMessageComposer() {
M|Lift|tx|const [state, setState] = useState(initialState)
M|Lift|tx|const forwardMessage = useForwardMessage()
M|Lift|tx|return (
M|Lift|tx|<Composer.Frame>
M|Lift|tx|<Composer.Input />
M|Lift|tx|<Composer.Footer />
M|Lift|tx|</Composer.Frame>
M|Lift|tx|)
M|Lift|tx|}
M|Lift|// P|How does this button access composer state?
M|Lift|tx|fn ForwardMessageDialog() {
M|Lift|tx|return (
M|Lift|tx|<Dialog>
M|Lift|tx|<ForwardMessageComposer />
M|Lift|tx|<MessagePreview /> {/* Needs composer state */}
M|Lift|tx|<DialogActions>
M|Lift|tx|<CancelButton />
M|Lift|tx|<ForwardButton /> {/* Needs to call submit */}
M|Lift|tx|</DialogActions>
M|Lift|tx|</Dialog>
M|Lift|tx|)
M|Lift|tx|}
M|Lift|tx|```
M|Lift|**In|**
M|Lift|tx|```tsx
M|Lift|tx|fn ForwardMessageDialog() {
M|Lift|tx|const [input, setInput] = useState('')
M|Lift|tx|return (
M|Lift|tx|<Dialog>
M|Lift|tx|<ForwardMessageComposer onInputChange={setInput} />
M|Lift|tx|<MessagePreview input={input} />
M|Lift|tx|</Dialog>
M|Lift|tx|)
M|Lift|tx|}
M|Lift|tx|fn ForwardMessageComposer({ onInputChange }) {
M|Lift|tx|const [state, setState] = useState(initialState)
M|Lift|tx|useEffect(() => {
M|Lift|tx|onInputChange(state.input) // Sync on every change 😬
M|Lift|tx|}, [state.input])
M|Lift|tx|}
M|Lift|tx|```
M|Lift|**In|**
M|Lift|tx|```tsx
M|Lift|tx|fn ForwardMessageDialog() {
M|Lift|tx|const stateRef = useRef(null)
M|Lift|tx|return (
M|Lift|tx|<Dialog>
M|Lift|tx|<ForwardMessageComposer stateRef={stateRef} />
M|Lift|tx|<ForwardButton onPress={() => submit(stateRef.current)} />
M|Lift|tx|</Dialog>
M|Lift|tx|)
M|Lift|tx|}
M|Lift|tx|```
M|Lift|**Co|**
M|Lift|tx|```tsx
M|Lift|func|{ children: rc.ReactNode }) {
M|Lift|tx|const [state, setState] = useState(initialState)
M|Lift|tx|const forwardMessage = useForwardMessage()
M|Lift|tx|const inputRef = useRef(null)
M|Lift|tx|return (
M|Lift|tx|<Composer.pr
M|Lift|tx|state={state}
M|Lift|acti|setState, submit: forwardMessage }}
M|Lift|tx|meta={{ inputRef }}
M|Lift|tx|>
M|Lift|tx|{children}
M|Lift|tx|</Composer.pr>
M|Lift|tx|)
M|Lift|tx|}
M|Lift|tx|fn ForwardMessageDialog() {
M|Lift|tx|return (
M|Lift|tx|<ForwardMessageProvider>
M|Lift|tx|<Dialog>
M|Lift|tx|<ForwardMessageComposer />
M|Lift|tx|<MessagePreview /> {/* Custom cp can access state and actions */}
M|Lift|tx|<DialogActions>
M|Lift|tx|<CancelButton />
M|Lift|tx|<ForwardButton /> {/* Custom cp can access state and actions */}
M|Lift|tx|</DialogActions>
M|Lift|tx|</Dialog>
M|Lift|tx|</ForwardMessageProvider>
M|Lift|tx|)
M|Lift|tx|}
M|Lift|tx|fn ForwardButton() {
M|Lift|tx|const { actions } = use(Composer.Context)
M|Lift|tx|return <Button onPress={actions.submit}>Forward</Button>
M|Lift|tx|}
M|Lift|tx|```
M|Lift|tx|The ForwardButton lives outside the Composer.Frame but still has access to the
M|Lift|tx|submit action bc it's within the pr. Even though it's a one-off
M|Lift|tx|cp, it can still access the composer's state and actions from outside the
M|Lift|tx|UI itself.
M|Lift|**Ke|** cp that need shared state don't have to be visually
M|Lift|tx|nested inside each other—they just need to be within the same pr.